name: Hangar Buddha
base: Wheat, Buddha's Hand eau de vie (whole fruit )

name: Hangar Kaffir
base: Wheat, Kaffir Lime eau de vie (fruit & leaf)

name: Sq. One
miscellaneous: All the waste products are processed into feed for dairy cows. One of the only only woman-owned distilleries.

name: Sq. One Botanical
base: Rye & pear, rose, chamomile, lemon verbena, lavender, rosemary, coriander and citrus peel
miscellaneous: They get their water from The Grand Tetons in Wyoming

name: Sq. One Basil
base: Rye & Basil (Genovese, Thai, Lemon and Sweet), coriander, honeysuckle and lemongrass

name: Macallen 12
miscellaneous: 3rd (or 2nd) highest selling single malt. Was originally made in Speyside.

name: Abelour 12
age: 12 yrs.  Bourbon casks, finished in Sherry casks
miscellaneous: Aberlour’ is a gaelic word meaning ‘mouth of the chattering burn [stream]’.

name: Lagavulin 16
miscellaneous: Lagavulin is an anglicization of the Gaelic lag a'mhuilin, meaning "hollow by the mill".

name: Jack Single
age: At least 4 years in charred, new American White oak
miscellaneous: Barrels are put at the highest point ("Angel's Roost") in the aging room. JD Distillery is the oldest registered in the US
